parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic power steering system can cause the vehicle to become difficult to steer, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering warning light illuminates
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering assist
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle surges while moving forward
the speedometer stops working
and the tachometer malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle stalls or loses power
electrical issues
warning lights on the dashboard
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience electrical issues, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
electrical issues
warning lights on the dashboard
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, experience difficulty shifting gears, or stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle stalls or loses power
and the vehicle may not start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly or not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag light comes on
the airbags deploy unexpectedly
or the airbags do not deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the interior door handle can cause the driver or passenger to become trapped inside the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The interior door handle breaks or fractures
making it impossible to exit the vehicle without rolling down the window and using the outside handle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power and become difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting of the inner bumper can cause the bumper to detach from the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The inner bumper is severely rusted
and when touched
it disintegrates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaking into the vehicle can cause electrical failures, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Water is leaking into the vehicle from the windshield
and the computer board has become wet.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Peeling of Front and Rear Bumpers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of the front and rear bumpers can cause the bumpers to detach from the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The front and rear bumpers are peeling
and no other part of the car is affected.
